snippet.textDisplay: Agreed 100%, they did what they could after TLJ, and it was better than I thought it would be. Now they have a leveled ground from where they can continue, or go to different directions in the next movies. I liked what they did with the new crew Poe, Finn, Rey and Kylo, leaving me finally wanting to see more of them, and learning about their characters. I even liked the new characters Zorri Bliss and Jannah. And I believe they did right with Chewbacca, 3PO, R2D2 (not so much screen time for him but it's ok), Luke, Lando, Palpatine, which was my biggest fear. And of course, I felt they treated the character of Leia after Carrie Fisher's passing with respect, I appreciated that they had her daughter Billie Lourd around whenever they used Carrie's footage. This felt like a good conclusion to the trilogy, and that they did their best to try to save the legacy of Star Wars going forward. Good job JJ and the team. May the Force be with us all.
snippet.textOriginal: Agreed 100%, they did what they could after TLJ, and it was better than I thought it would be. Now they have a leveled ground from where they can continue, or go to different directions in the next movies. I liked what they did with the new crew Poe, Finn, Rey and Kylo, leaving me finally wanting to see more of them, and learning about their characters. I even liked the new characters Zorri Bliss and Jannah. And I believe they did right with Chewbacca, 3PO, R2D2 (not so much screen time for him but it's ok), Luke, Lando, Palpatine, which was my biggest fear. And of course, I felt they treated the character of Leia after Carrie Fisher's passing with respect, I appreciated that they had her daughter Billie Lourd around whenever they used Carrie's footage. This felt like a good conclusion to the trilogy, and that they did their best to try to save the legacy of Star Wars going forward. Good job JJ and the team. May the Force be with us all.

snippet.textDisplay:
Hated TLJ, and this didn't fare any better for me

The best I can put it is small moments of brilliance, packed in a cocoon of cluster-f@#kery.
The story is a rushed mess.
It actually feels like they took everything they found on the internet, and threw it at the script. What didn't fall off of it made it in to the movie. In terms of characters, they mostly fall flat.
Logic is almost none existent at this point. I know people come to its defense saying that its a fiction, but with the thing is that even fiction needs to have rules and logic that makes sense in its own world, in order for it to work. Otherwise there is nothing keeping it from becoming chaotic.

Most of what I saw was an afterthought, considering how fast it goes trough story beats, and tries desperately to do damage control after TLJ.

snippet.textDisplay:
It’s nice to hear a less hateful review of the movie but there’s just way too many stupid things in it for me to go see.
I didn’t like Force Awakens. I didn’t like any of the new characters. They’re just too nerdy and awkward which I get is how this generation is but not in my Star Wars movies.
I don’t go to see characters that are like me. Characters don’t have to be like you to be relatable. That’s what the original Star Wars did was make larger than life characters that on some levels were relatable and JJs idea of a high concept film is just so much like a 5 yo with crayons that I just can’t enjoy what He makes.
At the end of the day having JJ fix the train wreck that Rianne made was like asking a mortician to fix a botched heart surgery.
The damage is just going to be worse so you’re basically praising the mortician for making the corpse look better but it’s still dead

snippet.textDisplay: The problem with these movies is that they don’t bring anything new to the table. Yes they have new powers but don’t give any explanations nor do they go into new territory. Apart from the powers we’ve already seen everything these movies had to offer in the previous six except for a stormtrooper going rogue but doesn’t matter cuz in the end it didn’t mean shit. They are just action adventure and mystery ( the mystery comes from ray and figuring out her past ) where as the first six were action adventure mystery wisdom and knowledge ( key word KNOWLEDGE ) originally George Lucas wanted to go in and focus more about the force and the midichlorians giving us something new fresh and unexpected instead of taking bits and pieces from other characters in the saga to create what we have already seen before. And with that I’ll end it.                                           “Although I still think a Jedi would  never give up but that’s old school and this is the new school”— Mark Hamill
